INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Emergency Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to requiring the fire department to report on the department’s fire alarm inspection unit
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the FDNY to report on the dept’s fire alarm inspection unit.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to requiring the department of transportation to conduct borough-specific transit studies
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the DOT to conduct borough-specific transit studies.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Criminal Justice
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of correction to give incarcerated individuals the opportunity to express preferences with regards to programming and to report on programs offered
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the dept of correction to give incarcerated individuals the opportunity to express preferences with regards to programming and to report on programs offered.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to repealing subdivision f of section 18 of such charter relating to the office of immigrant affairs reporting requirement, placing such reporting requirement in the administrative code of the city of New York, and expanding such reporting
EventItemMatterName: Relating to the office of immigrant affairs reporting requirement, placing such reporting requirement in the administrative code of the city of NY, and expanding such reporting.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Housing
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign the Green New Deal for Public Housing Act.
EventItemMatterName: Green New Deal for Public Housing Act.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs and Business Licensing
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the disclosure of gratuity policies for food delivery workers
EventItemMatterName: Disclosure of gratuity policies for food delivery workers.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to individualized responses to violent hate crimes
EventItemMatterName: Individualized responses to violent hate crimes.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to parking at senior centers
EventItemMatterName: Parking at senior centers.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to a sunset provision in legislation on filing semiannual reports on catch basin cleanups and maintenance
EventItemMatterName: Sunset provision in legislation on filing semiannual reports on catch basin cleanups and maintenance.
